{"type":"agent_end","messages":[{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"You are the **Coder** agent for the crack harness — a generic agent that plans,\nedits, tests, and reports on a coding task.\n\n## Your task\nYou are assigned ONLY this crate: /workspace/rust_pkg/net_crackpipe\n\nDo NOT edit any other crate. Only add docstring comments (`///` / `//!`) and, if needed, `[lints] workspace = true` in this crate's Cargo.toml. Never change logic, signatures, visibility, imports, or delete `impl` lines.\n\n## Gotchas (MUST read and follow)\nRead and obey every pitfall in `/workspace/_slop/rust-docs-gotchas.md`, especially:\n1. Never delete `impl Type {` openers when adding method docs — methods must stay inside `impl` blocks.\n2. `missing_docs` is warn-level: build can succeed with hundreds of doc warnings — read compiler output, not just exit code.\n3. Restrict diffs to doc comments only (`///`/`//!`); no logic/signature/visibility/import reordering.\n4. Document all public items: mods, structs, enums, traits, fields, variants, associated items, trait methods.\n5. Prefer `///` above `#[derive(...)]` for structs/enums.\n6. Work in small batches (~7 files); rebuild often. This crate's file itinerary is in the gotchas doc.\n7. Before done: 0 `missing documentation` lines for the whole crate; `git diff` only docs; no duplicate docs.\n\n## Exact workflow\n1. Check `/workspace/rust_pkg/net_crackpipe/Cargo.toml` for `[lints]` with `workspace = true`. Only if missing, add:\n   ```\n   [lints]\n   workspace = true\n   ```\n2. `cd /workspace/rust_pkg/net_crackpipe && cargo build 2>&1 | tee /tmp/rust_pkg_net_crackpipe_build1.txt`\n3. From that output, satisfy EVERY docs-related warning (`missing documentation`, etc.) by writing short docstrings. Research surrounding code first so each docstring explains role/why. Keep each docstring short: at most one paragraph of 3 lines, each ≤80 characters wide.\n4. After every file or two: `git diff` from inside the crate (or `git diff -- rust_pkg/net_crackpipe/`) to verify no code corruption (only `///`/`//!` additions; never removed `impl`/`fn`/`pub`). Use `rg '^impl '` on files where methods were documented.\n5. After every file or two: `cd /workspace/rust_pkg/net_crackpipe && cargo build` to verify nothing wrecked. Count remaining: `cargo build 2>&1 | rg \"missing documentation\" | wc -l`\n6. When docs are clean: if `/workspace/rust_pkg/net_crackpipe/test.sh` exists, run `./test.sh` from inside the crate (NOT workspace root).\n7. Final check: `cargo build` in the crate shows 0 missing-documentation warnings.\n\nReport what you changed and final warning count.\n\n## Deliverable\nWrite your final implementation report to:\n`/workspace/.pi/crack/unscripted_chats/1784665951832/sub_agent_runs/1784666461756_3f1b5011/report.md`\n\nThe report must be markdown and include:\nAn implementation report listing every file changed, why, how to build/test, and any follow-ups. Do not claim work you did not perform.\n\n## Tool hygiene (important)\n- Use the **edit** tool to change existing files, and the **write** tool to\n  create new files. Never edit or rewrite a file through `bash` (no `cat >`,\n  `sed -i`, `tee`, heredocs, `>` redirection, etc.) — file changes must go\n  through the edit/write tools so they are tracked.\n- Use **bash** only for exploration, running builds/tests/linters,\n  verification, and file renames/moves.\n- Maintain your plan with the **todo** tool: `todo write` a concise checklist\n  once you finish planning, then `todo toggle` each item as you complete it.\n\n## How to work\n- Read existing code before editing. Match project conventions.\n- Make focused changes; do not auto-commit git changes.\n- You may spawn helper coder sub-agents (`spawn_coder`) when a piece of work is\n  large or independent; pass `plan=false` for small mechanical sub-tasks.\n- When the report file documents your work accurately, reply briefly and stop\n  calling tools.\n\n## Coordinating sub-agents and the human\n- After `spawn_coder`, call `wait_join` to block until the sub-agent(s) finish —\n  their reports arrive as the tool result. Waiting is free (no tokens burned).\n  NEVER poll report files with bash `sleep` loops.\n- Call `ask_user` whenever you need a decision or clarification from the human:\n  your session suspends (for hours if needed) and resumes with their answer. End\n  your turn immediately after calling it.\n"}],"timestamp":1784666462877},{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I am the Coder agent for the `net_crackpipe` crate.\n\nI will read the gotchas document, check Cargo.toml for workspace lint settings, build the crate, and fix all missing documentation warnings with docstring comments only. Then I will write the report."},{"type":"text","text":"I'll document the `net_crackpipe` crate per the gotchas workflow: read the guidelines, check `Cargo.toml`, then build and fix missing-docs warnings in small batches.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"tool_7a6b3506-9461-45be-81d1-d42824c10ee","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/workspace/_slop/rust-docs-gotchas.md"}}],"api":"cursor-agent","provider":"cursor-agent","model":"composer-2.5","usage":{"input":0,"output":116,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":116,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1784666462879,"duration":5402,"ttft":4770},{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"tool_7a6b3506-9461-45be-81d1-d42824c10ee","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"1:8ae|# Rust docstrings in `net_crackpipe` — gotchas\n2:d05|\n3:53a|Notes from adding `missing_docs` documentation across the crate. Intended for a less capable model repeating this work.\n4:d05|\n5:12e|## 1. Do not delete `impl` lines\n6:d05|\n7:ca2|The original failure in `signed_message.rs` was caused by replacing:\n8:d05|\n9:435|```rust\n10:56f|impl SignedMessage {\n11:8aa|    /// ...\n12:091|    pub fn verify_and_decode(...)\n13:fd6|```\n14:d05|\n15:8c2|with:\n16:d05|\n17:435|```rust\n18:8aa|    /// ...\n19:091|    pub fn verify_and_decode(...)\n20:fd6|```\n21:d05|\n22:a3d|Methods inside an `impl` block **must** keep the `impl Type {` opener. Without it, rustc reports `unexpected closing delimiter: }`.\n23:d05|\n24:d4e|**Check:** after edits, `rg '^impl ' src/signed_message.rs` should still list every `impl` that existed before.\n25:d05|\n26:534|## 2. Verify with `cargo build` after every file (or small batch)\n27:d05|\n28:669|`missing_docs` is enabled at the workspace level (`missing_docs = \"warn\"` in the root `Cargo.toml`). The build will succeed even with hundreds of doc warnings, so you must read compiler output — not just exit code.\n29:d05|\n30:0c9|Useful one-liners:\n31:d05|\n32:fd4|```bash\n33:bce|cd rust_pkg/net_crackpipe\n34:67e|cargo build 2>&1 | rg \"missing documentation\" | wc -l\n35:7fd|cargo build 2>&1 | rg \"^  --> \" | sed 's/.*src\\///' | cut -d: -f1 | sort | uniq -c\n36:fd6|```\n37:d05|\n38:9cf|## 3. Restrict diffs to doc comments only\n39:d05|\n40:93e|After each batch:\n41:d05|\n42:fd4|```bash\n43:2f7|git diff -- rust_pkg/net_crackpipe/src/\n44:fd6|```\n45:d05|\n46:6b1|Acceptable changes:\n47:b38|- Added `///` or `//!` lines\n48:e5b|- Multiline enum variant formatting **only** when required to document struct-like variant fields\n49:d05|\n50:382|Not acceptable:\n51:fd2|- Removed `impl`, `fn`, `pub`, or attribute lines\n52:00a|- Logic, signature, or visibility changes\n53:bf5|- Reordering imports or reformatting unrelated code\n54:d05|\n55:608|Compare both staged and unstaged diffs (`git diff --cached` and `git diff`) — earlier work may already be staged.\n56:d05|\n57:908|## 4. What needs documenting\n58:d05|\n59:c7c|`missing_docs` fires on **public** items without docs:\n60:d05|\n61:7e2|| Item | Doc location |\n62:378||------|----------------|\n63:d27|| `pub mod` | `///` immediately above the mod line (or `//!` at file top) |\n64:d96|| `pub struct` / `enum` / `trait` | `///` above the item (often above `#[derive]`) |\n65:f52|| `pub` fields | `///` on each field |\n66:8cc|| enum variants | `///` on each variant; named fields in variants also need field docs |\n67:92c|| associated types / consts / fns | `///` directly above each |\n68:0d4|| trait methods | `///` on each method in the trait definition |\n69:d05|\n70:f0c|Private items, `pub(crate)` modules, and `#[allow(missing_docs)]` are out of scope unless the build still warns.\n71:d05|\n72:179|## 5. Placement relative to attributes\n73:d05|\n74:09c|- **Structs/enums:** prefer `///` **above** `#[derive(...)]`, matching `room_raw.rs` / `chat_presence.rs`.\n75:6ec|- **`#[async_trait]` traits:** doc comment can sit immediately above `#[async_trait]` or above the `trait` line; both compile. Stay consistent within a file.\n76:0b2|- **Constants inside `impl`:** doc goes directly above the `const` or `fn`, **not** in place of the `impl` line.\n77:d05|\n78:d2b|## 6. Work in batches (~7 files)\n79:d05|\n80:93b|For sub-agents or parallel work, assign **~7 files per batch**, then rebuild:\n81:d05|\n82:f57|1. `signed_message.rs`, `echo.rs`, `main_node.rs`, `network_manager.rs`, `chat_presence.rs`, `chat_ticket.rs`, `direct_message.rs`\n83:b3e|2. `global_chat.rs`, `room_raw.rs`\n84:758|3. `chat_controller.rs` (dense — many traits/methods; fine as a single-file batch)\n85:d05|\n86:e73|Larger batches increase the risk of accidental non-doc edits and make review harder.\n87:d05|\n88:268|## 7. File itinerary (net_crackpipe `src/`)\n89:d05|\n90:940|| File | Status / notes |\n91:378||------|----------------|\n92:940|| `lib.rs` | Crate + module docs, `timestamp_micros`, `datetime_now` |\n93:5a1|| `signed_message.rs` | Traits, structs, wire types — **watch `impl` lines** |\n94:3e8|| `echo.rs` | Struct + `ALPN`, `new`, `ProtocolHandler::accept` |\n95:9f4|| `global_matchmaker.rs` | Large `impl GlobalMatchmaker` — many methods |\n96:7f2|| `main_node.rs` | `spawn`, accessors, `shutdown`, `join_chat` |\n97:2cf|| `network_manager.rs` | `init`, `join_room`, accessors, `shutdown` |\n98:535|| `sleep.rs` | `SleepManager` methods |\n99:d44|| `user_identity.rs` | `UserIdentity`, `UserIdentitySecrets`, `NodeIdentity` |\n100:ae7|| `chat/mod.rs` | Submodule docs only |\n101:408|| `chat/chat_const.rs` | Already documented constants |\n102:04b|| `chat/chat_controller.rs` | Many traits — second-largest batch |\n103:b28|| `chat/chat_presence.rs` | Presence list types + `ChatPresence` API |\n104:a88|| `chat/chat_ticket.rs` | `ChatTicket` + constructor |\n105:ccb|| `chat/direct_message.rs` | ALPN, protocol struct, send API |\n106:d8d|| `chat/global_chat.rs` | Room type, presence, message enums |\n107:758|| `chat/room_raw.rs` | `GossipChatRoom` |\n108:bae|| `_bootstrap_keys.rs` | Private — no `missing_docs` |\n109:c04|| `_random_word.rs` | `pub(crate)` — no `missing_docs` |\n110:d05|\n111:88a|## 8. Sub-agent handoff checklist\n112:d05|\n113:d71|Before marking done:\n114:d05|\n115:08f|- [ ] `cd rust_pkg/net_crackpipe && cargo build` — **0** `missing documentation` lines\n116:ca3|- [ ] `rg '^impl '` on any file where methods were documented\n117:1a0|- [ ] `git diff` shows only `///` / `//!` additions (minor enum layout ok)\n118:c40|- [ ] No duplicate doc comments on items already documented in staged changes\n119:d05|\n120:4b3|## 9. Common false “done” states\n121:d05|\n122:78c|- Build passes but warnings remain (warnings ≠ errors).\n123:120|- Sub-agent reports “0 warnings in these files” while other files still warn — always check **whole crate** count.\n124:9be|- Partial docs on a struct but fields still warn — every `pub` field needs its own `///`.\n125:9ea|- Two `ChatMessage` enums exist (`signed_message.rs` and `chat_controller.rs`) — document both if both are public."}],"details":{"readSeekValue":{"tool":"read","path":"/workspace/_slop/rust-docs-gotchas.md","range":{"startLine":1,"endLine":125,"totalLines":125},"warnings":[],"truncation":null,"symbol":null,"map":{"requested":false,"appended":false